cauldon-lowe |title=Steaming back to Cauldon Lowe |newspaper=Heritage Railway |date=25 November 2010}}</ref> In 2014 this plan was placed on hold as the [[Competition Commission]] ruled that [[Lafarge Tarmac]] must sell one of its sites, possibly Caldon Low, so the heritage railway, the [[Churnet Valley Railway]], are seeking to purchase the line themselves.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leek-news.co.uk/LJ-Trains/story-20797980-detail/story.html |title=Leek railway line moves a step closer |newspaper=Leek Post & Times |date=12 March 2014 |access-date=23 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419015833/http://www.leek-news.co.uk/LJ-Trains/story-20797980-detail/story.html |archive-date=19 April 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Route==\n{{Historical Rail Start}}\n{{rail line|previous={{rws|Ipstones}}<br><small>[[Waterhouses branch line|Waterhouses branch]]</small>|col=800000 |next={{rws|Leek}}<br><small>[[Churnet Valley Line]]</small>|route=[[North Staffordshire Railway]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==References==\n* {{Quick-Stations |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Christiansen |first1=Rex |last2=Miller |first2=Robert William |title=The North Staffordshire Railway |year=1971 |publisher=David & Charles |location=[[Newton Abbot]], [[Devon]] |isbn=0-7153-5121-4 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Christiansen |first1=Rex |title=Portrait of the North Staffordshire Railway|year=1997|publisher=Ian Allan |location=[[Shepperton]], [[Surrey]] |isbn=0-7110-2546-0 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Jeuda |first1=Basil |title=The Leek, Caldon & Waterhouses Railway |year=1980 |publisher=North Staffordshire Railway Company (1978) |location=[[Cheddleton]], [[Staffordshire]]|isbn=0-907133-00-2 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Jeuda |first=Basil |title= The North Staffordshire Railway in LMS days |volume=3 |publisher= Lightmoor Press |location=[[Lydney]], [[Gloucestershire]] |year=2014 |isbn=978-1899889-83-9 |ref=harv}}\n\n{{Closed stations S